In charge of our next episode is one of Japan's leading, and very acclaimed, techno stalwarts, GO HIYAMA. Co-founder of Hue Helix and a veteran since the 90s, his detailed sound and exquisite productions are catalogued amongst the best of the best – <a href="http://www.beatport.com/track/servant-original-mix/1131983" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">Planet Rhythm</a>, <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WzBeRPMXjt8" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">Warm Up</a>, <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=voLCWgNUIFY" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">Audio Assault</a>, <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8uC5ZJ5j_bE" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">Perc Trax</a>, <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2XT36stDJWE" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">Stroboscopic</a>, and <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ywI93HXSDKU" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">Token</a>. For the occasion, he was kind enough to put together a fantastic beast of a mix for us, pushing 40 tracks in just over 70 minutes. Hypnotic, powerful and simply delightful, this is the real deal - Go Hiyama, folks. Enjoy!&#13;
