Following up our extremely successful last episode, we are back with the core sound that defines the series: deep, thought-providing techno. This time at the helm we have the riveting Dutch duo, ABSTRACT DIVISION, featuring part of their live set recorded a few weeks back at <a href="https://www.facebook.com/events/179143955616096/" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">Mental Evolution</a> in Utrecht, Netherlands. &#13;
&#13;
Paul Boex and Dave Miller are the veteran minds behind the project and their combination, marrying quality with experience from both ends, culminates in an extremely refined style. All of their productions, released mostly on their own <a href="http://www.discogs.com/label/123705-Dynamic-Reflection" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">Dynamic Reflection</a> founded by Paul back in 2008, are sophisticated, evoking, and ethereal – both for the mind and the body. In their own words: <i>“intelligent, dancefloor-oriented techno in its purest form.”</i> We are very glad to have them be part of the series. This is Abstract Division live, folks. Enjoy!&#13;
