After a couple of remarkable podcasts by veteran techno stalwarts, Episode 36 comes from young and talented producer, DEEPBASS. His name fittingly represents the essence and rhythm of this 1-hour techno hecatomb and includes a stellar tracklist with brand new material, as he says: <i>“from myself, my friends, and some artists I'm loving at the moment, and some older stuff for good measure, a good example of the kind of stuff I play in my live shows.”</i>&#13;
 &#13;
Darren has been busy in the studio, recently releasing the Analysis EP on Aconito Records (which is superb and in this mix) along with another EP on his own label, <a href="http://www.youtube.com/user/InformaRecords" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">Informa Records</a> (INFORMA006), with an original track by his friend Hironori Takahashi, a remix by Deepbass, and a still-undisclosed guest remixer. Also due on Informa will be a yet-to-be-announced Deepbass collaborative project. In addition, Darren has remixes coming out for Bleak on the new Glasgow-based label, Animal Farm Records, as well as for Lui Urbano on Ketra Records. And he is finalizing, as we speak, the 3rd Deepbass &amp; Ness collaboration.&#13;
