For Podcast Episode #31 we welcome aboard pivotal member of the recently established and acclaimed Techno label, Krill Music, and one of the rising South American figures within the genre, ESPEN LAURITZEN. In this great and very well crafted 1-hour mix he showcases his deep style and features the upcoming releases on Krill.&#13;
&#13;
&#13;
-&#13;
<a href="http://www.residentadvisor.net/dj/espenlauritzen" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">Espen Lauritzen</a>, one of the driving forces behind Krill Music, was born in Norway but moved at age 2 to South America (Argentina) where he was raised. Being always strongly impregnated by music, in mid-2000 he became a regular DJ at Cocoliche, the only Techno club in Buenos Aires. There is where he met his first heavyweight artists from the Techno international and national scene.&#13;
&#13;
<a href="http://www.krillmusic.com/" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">Krill Music</a> is a young Argentinean label founded in late 2011, when it debuted with the <a href="http://www.residentadvisor.net/review-view.aspx?id=10007" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">'Transparent / Anklad'</a> by <a href="https://www.facebook.com/pages/AnD/139500879474982" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">AnD</a> and <a href="https://www.facebook.com/JonasKoppMusic?ref=ts&amp;fref=ts" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">Jonas Kopp</a>. Throughout the year, the label has released three albums and promises to play an important role in the future of the Argentinian Techno scene. For its fourth release, the label welcomes the young artist from Italy, <a href="https://www.facebook.com/raffaele.attanasio2?fref=ts" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">Raffaele Attanasio</a>, who in turn introduces his new pseudonym 'X501' and a 'Bleak' Rework. For the 5th release, Krill Music is putting together a special release composed of 8 different artists and a double vinyl to celebrate its first year of life.&#13;
